---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { contactEmail } from '../../i18n/utils';
---

<LegalLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy"
  description="TrailSnag's privacy policy: what a report contains, where the data lives, and your rights."
  updated="Version of July 18, 2026"
>
  <p>
    TrailSnag is a trail-issue reporting platform. This policy covers this site and the app
    (<a href="https://trailsnag.app">trailsnag.app</a>). It is deliberately short: we collect
    little, and we say so plainly.
  </p>

  <h2>This website</h2>
  <p>
    This site is fully static. It uses no cookies, no audience analytics, and no advertising
    trackers. It is hosted on GitHub Pages, whose servers may keep technical logs (IP addresses)
    for security purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>What a report contains</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>the GPS position of the problem (or, failing that, the position of the scanned sticker);</li>
    <li>a category and, if you choose, a description and photos;</li>
    <li>a technical identifier generated by your device, which prevents duplicates.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    No account is required and reports are anonymous by default. Position and photos can be
    personal information: we treat them as such.
  </p>

  <h2>What we do with it</h2>
  <p>
    A report is transmitted only to the organization that manages the land in question, so it can
    triage and fix the problem. An organization may publish a public map of its reports: it shows
    the nature, position, and status of the problem — never the identity of the person who reported
    it. We sell no data, to anyone.
  </p>

  <h2>Where the data lives</h2>
  <p>
    The database and photo storage are in Canada (Montréal); the API is hosted in Toronto. Some of
    our technical providers (hosting, storage) are US companies subject to their own laws.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under Québec's Law 25, you may request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal
    information tied to a report you made. Write to the person in charge of the protection of
    personal information: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    The service evolves and this policy will evolve with it. Each version is dated; the version in
    force is the one published on this page.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
